<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old San Diego man was shot to death early Monday in the 4300 block of 
Bancroft Street. 
</P>
<P>
Police found Jose Angel Osuna, a native of Mexico, seriously wounded after they 
were called at 4:40 a.m. to investigate reports of gunshots. 
</P>
<P>
After administering first aid, police rushed Osuna to Mercy Hospital, where he 
died shortly after arrival. Osuna was a transvestite, police spokesman Bill 
Robinson said. He said the police have no one in custody and are continuing to 
investigate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
