<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: NATIONAL CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire caused $400,000 in damage to three stores late Sunday night, but no one 
was injured. 
</P>
<P>
Three fire companies answered the 10 p.m. call at a small shopping mall in the 
3400 block of East Plaza Boulevard. It took about 30 minutes to bring the fire 
under control, said Nancy Ruland of the National City Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
Lita Crone, who owns Lita's Hairstyling nearby, said the three businesses 
destroyed were Milo Beauty and Barber Supply, Late Night Video, and Tae Kwon 
Do. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070390-0024 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 242094 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 3, 1990, Tuesday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 4; Column 2; Metro Desk 
</P>
