SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man was struck and killed in the northbound lanes of Interstate 
805 just south of Imperial Avenue in San Diego early Monday morning, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
According to Joe Wolf, a California Highway Patrol officer, a northbound driver 
who saw the man walking west across the freeway about 6 a.m. swerved, but hit 
him anyway. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, estimated to be 35 years old, was dead at the scene. 
</P>
