<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. ADMINISTRATION SUSPENDS DIALOGUE WITH ARAFAT'S PLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The decision to suspend talks with the PLO as announced by President Bush is 
commendable. How can we continue to communicate with an organization that does 
not denounce terrorism enacted by a faction of its movement? 
</P>
<P>
Now to be fair and equitable, courageous and objective, the President has to 
suspend diplomatic relations with the government in Tel Aviv until Israel stops 
shooting teen-agers, tear-gassing infants, breaking stone-throwers bones, 
blowing up houses, deporting residents, silencing poets, starving villages, 
financing illegal acquisitions and settling refugees in the occupied 
territories. 
</P>
<P>
The President knows that statehood does not legitimize terrorism. Stop the flow 
of U.S. funds to Israel and see if Israeli officials will be motivated to call 
the White House for peace talks. 
</P>
<P>
ZAVEN KHANJAIN 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
