</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Twin Peaks' News: Fans of the quirky soap opera "Twin Peaks" can now do more 
than watch the show -- they can read the newsletter over cherry pie and coffee. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Ryan of Fullerton has started Twin Peaks Gazette, a quarterly publication 
of the Twin Peaks Appreciation Society. He said the newsletter will be "devoted 
to news and information on the series and the work of David Lynch," as well as 
serve as a "forum for the exchange of information among subscribers." 
Subscriptions are $8 a year and available by writing Ryan at 1557 Avenida 
Selva, Fullerton, Calif. 92633. GREG BRAXTON 
