<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: ROME; 
</P>
<P>
TEARS AND CHEERS IN ITALY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fully half the people on Earth are expected to witness the final on Sunday of 
this year's World Cup, the monthlong soccer orgy that is the globe's most 
popular sporting event. 
</P>
<P>
The total TV audience for the 52-match spectacular may reach 26 billion. 
</P>
<P>
Of the original 24 hopefuls in a quadrennial tournament, that will be played in 
the United States for the first time in 1994, four now remain. Host Italy meets 
defending champion Argentina in Naples tonight, and on Wednesday in Turin, West 
Germany meets England. 
</P>
<P>
Oddsmakers predict an Italy -- West Germany cup final in Rome. 
</P>
