</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marion Hughes Newkirk, an area activist who served as president of the Friday 
Morning Club from 1957 to 1961 and who also founded Operation Moral Upgrade, a 
group of women concerned with what they saw as the fading moral standards of 
the day, is dead. 
</P>
