</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Landlord Devanand Sharma, recently convicted for slum conditions at a Westlake 
apartment building he owns, was sentenced Monday to perform community service, 
fined $3,000 and placed on probation. 
</P>
<P>
A Municipal Court jury had found Sharma guilty of 23 criminal counts related to 
slum conditions at the building at 737 Westlake Ave. in Los Angeles. Problems 
included lack of heat, broken windows and vermin infestation. 
</P>
