<P>
BOMBS WRECK BANK, TWO OFFICES IN SPAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA CORUNA, Spain 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three bombs wrecked a bank and two employment offices in the northwestern 
Spanish ports of La Coruna and El Ferrol on Monday, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
No one was hurt. Officials said the attacks bore the hallmarks of the 
little-known Guerrilla Army of the Free Galician People, which campaigns for 
the independence of the impoverished northwestern region of Galicia. 
</P>
