70 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: INVESTOR LOWERS HIS STAKE IN TOOLWORKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Connecticut investor John R. Purcell lowered his stake in Software Toolworks 
Inc. to 4.3% of the Chatsworth company's stock from 5.3%. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Purcell said he sold 
200,000 shares June 22 for $17 each, or $3.4 million. He now owns 856,474 
shares, the filing said. 
</P>
<P>
Software Toolworks makes software for the Nintendo home-video system and 
personal computers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA070390-0126 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 242352 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
July 3, 1990, Tuesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
