<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: DICK CLARK PRODUCTIONS GETS JAPANESE CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dick Clark Productions Inc. said it received a $4.5-million contract from 
Campaign Dynamics in Tokyo to secure performers for 10 concerts to be held in 
Japan under Dick Clark's American Music Awards trademark. 
</P>
<P>
Terms call for Campaign Dynamics to pay for the concerts, including staging and 
promotional costs. Burbank-based Dick Clark, in addition to its fee for booking 
the talent, would retain television rights to show the concerts in all 
worldwide markets except Japan. 
</P>
<P>
The concerts will be held next spring at the Yokohama Arena in Yokohama, Japan, 
the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
