LOVE/HATE: The Rams have been here for 10 years now (C1), and at times there 
was little love lost between player and fan. . . . Players have described 
county fans as bland as white bread -- and Coach John Robinson once said his 
team played better on the road without the fans. . . . A poll last winter 
showed that in Orange County, about a third of the people wouldn't miss the 
Rams if they moved and another third weren't sure. Mark I. Pinsky and Martin 
Beck 
