<TEXT>
<P>
Product line sold: Pacific Scientific Co., an aerospace and industrial products 
manufacturer in Newport Beach, has sold its line of sensitive relay products to 
Communications Instruments Inc. in Fairview, N.C., for $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
The product line accounted for $3 million in sales in 1989. Richard V. Plat, a 
Pacific Scientific spokesman, said the company sold the operation because it 
wants to concentrate on its line of products for the electric utility industry. 
</P>
<P>
Communications Instruments plans to build the Sigma relay lines at its plant in 
North Carolina. 
