<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New headquarters: Novadyne Computer Systems Co., formerly McDonnell Douglas 
Field Services Co., will build a new headquarters in Santa Ana to house the 300 
people working for the company at three sites in Orange County, spokeswoman Pat 
Dwight said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas Corp. said Sunday that it had sold the computer maintenance 
and distribution division to a management-led investor group for $65 million. 
The company, which has 1,000 employees nationwide, has no plans for changes in 
its employment levels, Dwight said. 
</P>
<P>
Bert Novak, president and chief executive of Novadyne, began negotiating the 
buyout 11 months ago with McDonnell Douglas. Novadyne has more than $100 
million in revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
