<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: VENTURA COUNTY HOUSE SALES UP 23% FOR QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sales of new single-family houses in Ventura County in the second quarter rose 
23% from the first quarter but remained 48% below the sales pace of a year 
earlier, a real estate research firm said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended June 30, 383 new detached houses were sold, up from 
312 in the January-March period of this year but down from 733 units sold in 
the second quarter of 1989, The Meyers Group reported. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the median price for a new single-family house in Ventura County was 
$337,500 in the latest quarter, down 5% from $354,990 in the first quarter but 
up 2% from $329,950 a year earlier, Meyers said. The median price means half 
the houses sold for more than that price, and half sold for less. 
</P>
</TEXT>
