<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: TRANSTECHNOLOGY LOSES $4.63 MILLION IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TransTechnology Corp., a defense and industrial products concern based in 
Sherman Oaks, posted a $4.63-million fiscal fourth-quarter loss and suspended 
its quarterly dividend. 
</P>
<P>
The loss in the quarter ended March 31, which TransTechnology had predicted, 
contrasted with a $5.26-million profit a year earlier and came on a 13% drop in 
revenue to $62.4 million from $71.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
TransTechnology said the latest loss included a $3-million loss from operations 
and $10 million to $12 million in writedowns, mainly to lower the value of its 
inventory. 
</P>
<P>
For the full year, TransTechnology lost $8.44 million on revenue of $198.5 
million. The previous year, it earned $9.24 million on revenue of $219 million. 
</P>
<P>
TransTechnology said it suspended its common-share dividend as part of a 
revised credit arrangement with its bank lenders. The company last paid a 
dividend of 24 cents a share in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
